Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Composer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-7)

To find or replace a word in the Composer document, click on the respective tab "Search &amp; Replace" in the right panel. Only looking for words in the document click into the Search form field and provide a desired word. There are some search options, helping to shrink the result set. For replacing click on the replace tab, and provide a word, which will replace the founded ones. You can choose to replace words either individually or everything at once.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Find and Replace tab*

## Available search options in the Composer
- Match case

- Match whole word

> Only matches the full desired word(s), so parts from other words will be excluded.

- Match cyclic

> This option is not explicitly available in the Composer as it is set by default - search searches cyclic in the document so that after last result comes the first result again.
